<br>
I have a few comments regarding your newest post.<br>
<br>
I believe you have a misconception about wizards as a class.<br>
<br>
You mention that tanks need clerics and that it is really two people dealing out damage.  Well wizards in groups need tanks, healer, and enchanters or bards to do their damage.  Healer damage is not 2:1 There are usually more than one tank per healer. Tanks are able to sustain their damage without much aid wereas wizards actually need MORE support than the tanks.  The conclusion you seem to want to come to is that wizards are standalone damage.  They are not.  Please rethink this.<br>
<br>
You seem to think wizards are cabable of doing significantly more damage at the right moment in time to mobs.  Later in the game (51+) Wizards do NOT accomplish this task with any sort of 'significance.'  If a mob is 'running' then theres already something going wrong.  Even if a mob is running, a standard wizard spell (draught) often STILL wont be able to stop the mob any faster than the tanks in that period of time.  Not only does the wizard get to spend a few bubbles of mana doing this which they have to spend medding back but they don't do it with any sort of efficiency.  Please rethink your approach to this matter as well.<br>
<br>
If you were to enable a wizard to do more damage with what mana they are given, say by a very efficient low damage but very low mana cost spell- (ie 300dmg for 30mana 2sec) at say level 55... (or something of the sort) How would this unbalance them?  They couldn't do too much damage in too short of time... they would still have to control their agro... but they wouldn't have to spend as much time medding to recover AND could contribute to the long battles as they should be able to.<br>
<br>
Those are my thoughts.  I hope they are of use.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwraithwavefeaamael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wraithwave FeaAmael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 392<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 9:03 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thoughts on Absors latest post</span><hr size=1> The one key missing point is that when executed properly (i.e. timing of pulls and medding) the tank/cleric combination can pull indefinitely.  Once a wizard does his job, he has to sit and med.  Yes, the cleric has to as well, but the tank can continue fighting even while the cleric is medding.  With excellent timing skills, you could simply pull forever without stopping.  Ask certain groups how they achieved 59-60 under two weeks.  You'll hear reports of non stop, high speed pulling.  But I have NEVER seen a wizard mentioned in those situations.  Except MAYBE for snaring.  And that isn't always the case.<br>
